Class Translation2d

  • java.lang.Object
    • frc.team670.robot.utils.math.Translation2d

    public class Translation2d
extends java.lang.Object
implements Interpolable<Translation2d>
    Taken from Team 254 2017 Robot Code. A translation in a 2d coordinate frame. Translations are simply shifts in an (x, y) plane.

        Description copied from interface: Interpolable
        Interpolates between this value and an other value according to a given parameter. If x is 0, the method should return this value. If x is 1, the method should return the other value. If 0 < x < 1, the return value should be interpolated proportionally between the two.
